# MIR (vendored) — in-process micro-JIT for the codegen RHS

This is a pruned vendor copy of [MIR](https://github.com/vnmakarov/mir) by
Vladimir Makarov, pinned at commit `99c65079` (MIT-licensed; see `LICENSE`).
MIR's own `README.md` is preserved alongside this file.

## Why it's here (GH #78)

bngsim's codegen backend emits good native-quality C for the ODE RHS
(`bngsim/python/bngsim/_codegen.py`), but pays a heavy *compile latency*:
`cc -O3` as a subprocess plus `dlopen` costs ~80 ms–seconds. That latency is
why the codegen threshold sits at N≥256 species and leaves the intermediate
band on the slower ExprTk-bytecode path.

MIR ships **c2mir**, a C11 frontend, so the *same C source `_codegen.py`
already emits* can be JIT-compiled in-process in ~1–2 ms — no subprocess, no
`.so`, no `dlopen`. It is a single ~1 MB C library (no LLVM, no Rust toolchain),
targeting x86-64 and aarch64 (Apple Silicon).

## What is built

Three translation units, gated behind the `BNGSIM_ENABLE_MIR` CMake option
(default OFF):

- `mir.c`        — MIR core (loader, linker, interpreter; `#include`s the
                   host target backend, e.g. `mir-x86_64.c`/`mir-aarch64.c`)
- `mir-gen.c`    — the optimizing JIT code generator
- `c2mir/c2mir.c`— the C11 → MIR frontend

Include dirs: this directory and `c2mir/`.

## The header-free-source rule

c2mir's bundled preprocessor cannot parse the platform SDK `<math.h>` /
`<stdlib.h>` — they use compiler-specific extensions (on macOS c2mir reports
*"Unsupported compiler detected"* and chokes on the SDK `math.h`).

Because bngsim *generates* the C it JITs, the JIT path sidesteps this entirely:
it strips the `#include <...>` lines from the generated source and prepends
`extern` declarations for the libc/libm symbols the RHS can call (`pow`, `exp`,
`sqrt`, `log`, `fabs`, `fmax`, `fmin`, `memset`, …). MIR resolves those externals
at link time through the import resolver, which calls `dlsym(RTLD_DEFAULT, name)`.
See `bngsim/include/bngsim/mir_jit.hpp`.

## Refreshing

Use `bngsim/scripts/vendor_mir.py` — it prunes the tree from a MIR checkout at
the pinned commit in `VENDOR.json` and re-anchors the per-file checksums.
`--summary` previews, `--check` is the offline tripwire that the checked-in tree
still matches `VENDOR.json`. See `bngsim/scripts/MIR_VENDORING.md` for the full
refresh + MIR-on build/validation flow.
